description.0: A look ahead at Groo! Plus, previews of the WEB OF SPIDER-MAN and the deluxe Marvel Universe handbook.
description.2: Conan and this mercenary army stumble into a deadly war between the immortal and the undead!
description.3: Tabloid reporter Jake Jones manages to get a career-making photograph; Spider-Man unmasked! With his secret identity on the line, will Spider-Man teach this morally bankrupt journalist a lesson? You bet!
description.4: Abandoning his physical form, the Vision sends his mind into the world computer network and begins to take it over. Unexpectedly, he encounters another living intelligence trapped therein! Enter: The Mad Thinker!
description.5: Without his shield, is Captain America any match for Batroc's Brigade?
description.6: Captain Britain takes on the Slaymaster! Also, the source of Captain Britain's power is revealed!
description.7: Luke, Leia and Han find themselves up to their ears in fur-coated trouble when they get caught in the middle of a bloody conflict between two fanatic factions of a race of cat-people!
description.8: The contents of Llrrllllnnllyyrrl's dowry are uncovered…as is the true identity of the Sorcerer!
description.11: Leave it to Mike Zeck to draw a Dr. Doom who looks both like he's been beaten to within an inch of his life, yet could easily take on a god. Hmm...he kinda did, didn't he?
description.15: The past collides with the present when Matt starts having prophetic dreams about the Wild West. Featuring an alternate timeline story with Two-Gun Kid, gunslinger of Arizona!
description.16: Things go awry when Hulk tries to find his next meal. Plus, the U-Foes escape!
description.17: Guest starring Tigra! The conflict between Rhodey and Tony Stark reaches its peak. Rhodey moves out and heads for the West Coast Avengers' estate in California. And Tony Stark faces his most fateful decision of all; should he don his armor again?
description.19: She-Hulk feels the sting of fame when scandalous photos of her are snapped. Can she halt printing before being humiliated on the newsstand? Meanwhile, things really heat up between Johnny and Alicia!
description.20: After the crazed magician Kulan Gath turns Manhattan into a barbarian fantasyland X-Men must stop the ancient wizard from doing permanent harm.
description.21: Protests and riots claim Abbotsford! Can the Defenders find the root cause for all this chaos?
description.23: Slaymaster and the Crazy Gang take Captain Britain hostage!
description.24: Prince Denin petitions help from Luke Skywalker, Princess Leia and the Rebel Alliance to fight the remnants of the Imperial forces. But this help is overshadowed by strange dreams involving Yoda, Ben Kenobi and Darth Vader!
description.27: A young scribe desperately searches for Conan to halt the end of the world!
description.29: Go beyond the Wraith War in this special first look…
description.31: The Hobgoblin goes for broke in his quest to put Spider-Man away forever! And it looks like nothing Spidey can do will stop him!
description.32: After an anti-mutant group burns down the home of the Vision and the Scarlet Witch, the android Avenger overcomes his indecision and prepares to implement his plan for world control! Who is fit to live in the new world order?
description.33: In this issue: Captain America goes up against Machete, a South American master of bladed weapons! Can Cap go toe-to-toe with this new enemy?
description.36: On his quest to save Tarianna from an evil sorcerer, Ben finds himself at Dracula's Castle!
description.43: Daredevil or Kingpin! Who will get to Micah Synn first? Don't miss the final confrontation that's been building for the last four issues!
description.44: Our hero is powerless as a slave to the Red Knights! A certain viridian vixen may be able to help Hulk out of this bind...
description.45: The Termite bites off even more to chew! Stark goes to the government to find a way to safely stop him! Iron Man takes off to find a deadly way to stop him! Guest starring: the Scarlet Witch!
description.46: Storm has brought the New Mutants to the island of Kirinos following their battle with the Shadow King. In Asgard, Loki looks down on Storm and admires her warrior strength and spirit. Will Loki and Enchantress mettle in the realm of Midgard to claim the New Mutants for Asgard?
description.48: The X-Men stage a rescue mission to retrieve Storm and the New Mutants from Asgard. But with Storm and the young mutants under the enchantment of Loki, has the X-team bit off more than they can chew?
description.49: The Thing vs. Frankenstein's Monster- and it's a Secret Wars tie-in!
description.50: Rachel and Magma are on Selene's tail when the energy vampire heads into the Hellfire Club. What business does the witch have with Sebastian Shaw?
description.52: When Smythe thinks Mary Jane is actually Spider-Man, both her and Peter will have to work together to take down the self-professed Spider-Slayer.
description.53: The Defenders fight off a surprise attack from Mantis! With all this chaos, will the Dragon of the Moon take the opportunity to control Moondragon?
description.59: This one’s got it all! A legion of Marvel’s top artists and writers offer an epic preview of Marvel Comics from 1985.
description.61: Wraal, the soul-devouring demon, is back! Conan barely defeated him before — can he do it again?
description.63: Has Chief Inspector Thomas discovered the true identity of Captain Britain?
description.64: The villain's name is Knife, and he's out to enslave the world of the Wookiees and Chewie's brother-in-law is helping him!
description.66: Harry Osborn, under attack by the Hobgoblin! Will Harry get a bail-out from the Friendly Neighborhood Spider-Man?
description.67: The Vision secretly plots with ISAAC to create a paradise on Earth by assuming personal control of all its computer systems. But will the Avengers catch on soon enough to stop their teammate's plans of world domination?
description.68: The Red Skull has been defeated! But Cap's not out of danger yet. With the combined efforts of Hank Pym and the Vision, the Avengers race against the clock to save Cap's life! But will their efforts prove successful when Mother Superior interrupts the de-aging process?
description.71: Ben and Tarianna are given the difficult task of delivering a pursued child back to his hometown.
description.74: As awesome and striking as Spider-Man's new black costume is, you can't help but stare at the crazy super-brawl taking place behind Spidey. Artist Mike Zeck nailed this cover, without a doubt.
description.78: DD's war on Synn continues; Foggy finds out how badly Micah mistreated his wife and tries to go to the rescue with DD as backup.
description.79: Hulk leaves Crossroads and enters a dimension where a beautiful, green-skinned woman cries tears that transform into flowers. Does Ol' Greenskin have a shot with this mystical lady?
description.80: It's the new Iron Man vs. the old Iron Man! Tony Stark wants his new armor back, but Rhodey refuses! Tony unearths one of his first Iron Man suits of armor!
description.82: Reed and his team uncover some interesting facts about the Other-Earth. Can Reed close the gap in his memory and be reunited with his father Nathaniel Richards, ruler of the Other-Earth?
description.83: To fight the mysterious shadowbeings Magik and Nightcrawler's main squeeze Amanda Sefton team up for a sorcery-infused battle for the ages!
description.84: Will the team stick together or will they cut ties? Will Graviton destroy them before the super-heroes even have a chance to decide? The heart-racing conclusion to the West Coast Avengers first series!
description.85: With Gargoyle's warning still in mind, the Defenders are divided on whether or not to trust Moondragon! Also: a new leader for the new Defenders!
description.89: Conan discovers pleasure and danger incarnate when he meets the voluptuous Snow Raven.
description.91: The long-hidden secrets of Mary Jane Watson's past finally revealed! And, if you thought Spidey had his hands full fighting the Hobgoblin before, wait till you see what happens now! Plus, new developments on Spidey's costume!
description.92: Maelstrom is back from the dead! And he's brought company; Helio, Phobius, and Gronk! Together the team of villains plot to gain absolute power by siphoning the energy of the Earth's rotation! The Avengers won't know what hit them!
description.93: This issue: It's a battle to the death! Captain America versus the Red Skull!
description.95: Steve Gerber and Val Mayerik discuss Void Indigo.
description.98: What will happen to Luke and Leia now that the rebels have won the war? It's a major turning point in the Star Wars saga-and it guest-stars Rik Duel! And the Kiro gang! And-hold onto yer hats-the Ewoks!
description.99: Tarianna is kidnapped by Grimm the Sorcerer and his minion, the Reckoner!

8.text: The contents of Llrrllllnnllyyrrl's dowry are uncovered…as is the true identity of the Sorcerer!

9.text: Spider-Man joins the X-Men to take down Juggernaut! The power of the Cyttorak grows in the mutants' fiercest foe, as all sides scramble to subdue Cain Marko.  Spider-Man has a change of heart about the X-Men- but why?

10.text: All aboard the Danish Princess! Doc Strange and Black Knight must protect the passengers on a luxury cruise from the arcane evils of Umar.

11.text: DEATH TO THE BEYONDER Though the heroes have successfully driven Galactus away, they find that their seeming victory has only sealed their fate.
Leave it to Mike Zeck to draw a Dr. Doom who looks both like he's been beaten to within an inch of his life, yet could easily take on a god. Hmm...he kinda did, didn't he?

12.text: Surtur versus Odin for the fate of Asgard! With the help of Mr. Fantastic and The Human Torch, can the Asgardians win the day? Or will the Shining City be enshrouded in endless winter?

13.text: Elizabeth Twoyoungmen transforms into her mutant alter ego – TALISMAN!

14.text: Peter Parker meets his new neighbors, and things promise to get interesting. While on their way to Kingpin, Spidey and Black Cat encounter the villainous Spot! Plus, Spider-Man's alien costume escapes from the Baxter Building!

22.text: Wolverine teaches Kitty the importance of willpower. Now she must make an important decision on how to deal with the violation of her mind.

25.text: What happened to Idiot and White Light following last issue? Plus, giant flying insects would scare anyone, but luckily for us, Iceman will save us all!

28.text: One's got power, the other's got punch, and when they team up in a fight to the finish against Control 7, it's pure pandemonium!

30.text: The kids' first day of school is filled with excitement and new friends, but what happens after school is even more jam-packed! The Power Pack kids meet Cloak and Dagger and join them against dragon robots!

35.text: Beast and Dazzler enter romantic territory while she recovers under his watch at the Heartbreak Hotel. Although her powers are still erratic, Daz agrees to a first performance at the ‘underground theater’…actually a mutant gladiatorial ring!

36.text: On his quest to save Tarianna from an evil sorcerer, Ben finds himself at Dracula's Castle!

37.text: Spidey and Cannonball of the New Mutants against the electrical menace of the Incandescent Man!

39.text: ASSAULT ON GALACTUS As the heroes make their last ditch effort against Galactus, Doctor Doom seizes the opportunity to grind them all under his heel.

40.text: The forces of Asgard battle Surtur and his minions! But if Surtur can best the Asgardian continent who will stand to oppose him in Asgard itself? Will it be Thor? Odin?

41.text: Heather tries to bring the old team back together, but receives backlash from previous members. Meanwhile, Shaman and his daughter investigate a possession…and Elizabeth's mutant powers manifest!

42.text: Kingpin drives a wedge between Spider-Man and Black Cat when the source of her 'bad luck powers' are revealed. Will Spidey ever see the Cat reform? Plus, the secret of the Spot discovered by one of Kingpin's scientists!

54.text: Dazzler just wants a fun night at the roller derby but a group of foul-mouthed ruffians called the Racine Ramjets have other plans!

55.text: Wolverine becomes the victim of a brainwashed Kitty Pryde.

57.text: Captain Hero is taken to Project Pegasus, but when Iron Fist goes there, he discovers that someone, or something, is loose and systematically killing everyone in the complex!

59.text: This one’s got it all! A legion of Marvel’s top artists and writers offer an epic preview of Marvel Comics from 1985.

62.text: After Iron Man 2020’s failed attack, Sunset Bain’s hordes feel the backlash. Machine Man and Jocasta are reunited.

65.text: Power Pack takes New York! The boys break off from the girls and meet Spider-Man while the wall-crawler's facing off against Dragon Man!

70.text: It’s mutant mayhem in full throttle as two X-Men star in an unlikely team-up! While on vacation from the Defenders, Beast runs into Dazzler on the Hollywood circuit. Recently outed as a mutant, and with her singing career up in smoke, Hank McCoy promises to have Dazzler’s back. But Dazzler has just signed a new contract…one that promises to get her center stage at an ‘experimental underground theater’!

71.text: Ben and Tarianna are given the difficult task of delivering a pursued child back to his hometown.

72.text: Spider-Man and Thor together against the Black Abbott and his savage Black Apostles in the culmination of the Black Abbott trilogy! The Black Abbott is out to steal the greatest prize of all, the powers of the mighty Thor! Plus, more developments on Spidey's costume!

73.text: The Black Knight has been resurrected along with the curse on his sword! Can he and the mystic Doctor Strange together battle the menacing Umar?

74.text: INVASION As the battle-weary heroes recuperate and repair their gear, Spider-Man makes make a discovery that will change his life and his costume!
As awesome and striking as Spider-Man's new black costume is, you can't help but stare at the crazy super-brawl taking place behind Spidey. Artist Mike Zeck nailed this cover, without a doubt.

75.text: Odin unveils the plan of attack as Surtur makes his way to Midgard. If the Asgardians cannot intercept his course, Surtur will wreak havoc alongside the Sons of Muspel. Little do the Asgardians know-they are playing right into Surtur's hands.

76.text: Heather Hudson becomes the new leader of Alpha Flight!

77.text: Introducing Marvel's most miserly character…The Hermit! Spider-Man encounters a man who just wants to left alone. No, really, The Hermit just wants to be alone.

86.text: Kitty Pryde has been turned into a brainwashed ninja assassin. Now it's up to Wolverine to bring Kitty back to the light and get to the bottom of the debacle with her father.

87.text: You know Bobby Drake, original X-Man, but now meet the rest of his one-of-a-kind family! The youngest of the X-Men steps out in his own solo adventure -- with no mutant teammates, no Defenders, and no Champions on back up!

90.text: Machine Man’s sanctuary is attacked by Arno Stark…and he’s got some mechanized backup courtesy of Sunset Bain!

94.text: Introducing special Government Security Agent Gordy! He's rough, he's tough and he's mean, and he's on our side! For Power Man and Iron Fist, he's pure poison!

96.text: Power Pack and Henry Gyrich come under fire when Carmody takes his investigation of the kids a little too far.

99.text: Tarianna is kidnapped by Grimm the Sorcerer and his minion, the Reckoner!
